<item>
            <title>[SOLR-976] deleteByQuery is ignored when deleteById is placed prior to deleteByQuery in a &lt;delete&gt; </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-976</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to the following if block, deleteByQuery cannot be executed. cmd.id and cmd.query should be set to null when UpdateProcessor chain is finished.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;RunUpdateProcessor&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void processDelete(DeleteUpdateCommand cmd) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;( cmd.id != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; ) {
    updateHandler.delete(cmd);
  }
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
    updateHandler.deleteByQuery(cmd);
  }
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.processDelete(cmd);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
